import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import statsmodels.api as sm
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.hist(data['cx'], bins='auto', edgecolor='black')
    plt.xlabel('Longitude')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    ax = plt.gca()
    ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('What is the distribution of longitude values in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
```

    plt.xlabel('Latitude')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    ax = data.plot.bar(x='name', y='cx', legend=False)
    max_longitude = data['cx'].max()
    max_borough = data.loc[data['cx'] == max_longitude, 'name'].iloc[0]
    ax.axhline(max_longitude, color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Max: {max_longitude:.2f} ({max_borough})')
    ax.legend()
    plt.title('Which borough has the highest longitude value?', wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
```
